Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula will outline his Department’s priorities for the 2019/20 financial year. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. CAPE TOWN - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula will outline his department’s priorities for the 2019/20 financial year. "As previously stated in my budget speech, we seek to not only fix transport for our people but work towards job creation and economic growth benefiting all, especially the youth," Mbalula said. The Minister is also set to announce the Department of Transport’s new Director-General. Mbalula has taken on several issues since his appointment, including tackling Cape Town's train issues and the Gauteng e-toll system. 